question.query: what projects are trending on base and solana

steps.text:
Here’s a quick snapshot of what’s trending right now on Base and Solana. Note that “trending” shifts fast; this is based on recent volume, headlines, and social chatter over the past couple of weeks.

Base
- Aerodrome (AERO): Still the top DEX on Base and expanding its footprint; remains a liquidity hub on the chain, including big cbBTC activity. Source: The Block reported Aerodrome’s upgrade/expansion push in Nov 2025 (the trend has carried into 2026).
  - https://www.theblock.co/post/378634/aerodrome-upgrades-evm-extensions-circles-arc-metadex
- Base memecoins: BRETT, TOSHI, SPX6900, RIBBITA/TIBBIR, NPC, NEIRO, REKT are among the bigger names that keep cycling through the “most watched” lists.
  - Overview lists: https://99bitcoins.com/analysis/best-base-chain-meme-coins/
  - Ranked Base meme caps (snapshot): https://coinranking.com/coins/base-meme
  - Toshi saw a major pump when Coinbase added it to its listing roadmap (signal of sustained interest): https://www.theblock.co/post/334650/base-memecoin-toshi-surges-coinbase-listing-roadmap-addition
- Creator/“social” coins on Base via Zora: Coinbase’s push into creator coins on Base has drawn attention (and some criticism) after high-profile launches spiked then slumped—still a hot topic on Base. Source:
  - https://cointelegraph.com/news/base-creator-coin-experiment-meets-resistance

Solana
- Memecoins leading flows: BONK and other SOL memes (WIF, POPCAT, BOME) have kicked off 2026 strong, with SOL meme trading volumes spiking to new highs.
  - Coindesk on record memecoin volumes: https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/01/06/solana-memecoin-frenzy-sends-pumpswap-trading-volume-to-record-usd1-2-billion
  - Sector-wide memecoin rally (BONK mentioned): https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/01/05/memecoin-comeback-talk-builds-as-doge-shib-bonk-rally-in-early-2026
  - Context on 2025’s Solana token-launch boom (fueling today’s meme churn): https://cryptoslate.com/solana-applications-generated-2-4-billion-proving-the-network-is-finally-decoupling-from-this-volatile-metric/
- Core trading/DeFi venues seeing steady usage:
  - Aggregation/DEX: Jupiter, Raydium
  - Perps: Drift
  - Lending/yield: Kamino, Meteora; liquid staking via Marinade; MEV staking via Jito
  These aren’t “memes,” but they consistently rank among Solana’s highest-usage apps by volume/TVL and benefit from the meme cycle spillover. (Cross-checks: Blockworks Analytics/DeFi dashboards and recent Solana ecosystem coverage.)
  - Blockworks Solana analytics hub: https://blockworks.co/analytics/solana

Want me to pull live “trending” pairs (top volume or most-viewed) for the last hour/day on Base and Solana from DEX trackers right now? If you tell me the timeframe (1h/24h/7d) and whether you want tokens or protocols, I’ll fetch a real-time list.
